Subject: Retrogaming
Description: Join us for Retro Gaming! Including systems from Atari to Game Cube and (almost) everything in between, join us for four hours of reliving your childhood! Enter our Mario Party 4 Tournament and win a retro system to take home!  Speakers include:Angie Rush - Track: Penguicon, Gaming  - Duration: 5 hours and 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Teens of the Wasteland
Description: Why do so many contemporary YA novels feature a post-apocalyptic setting with teens on a journey across what remains of civilization? What needs to these books fulfill, and has the wave of their popularity already peaked? If so, whats next?  Speakers include:Emmy Jackson, Jon David, Janice Leach, Angie Rush - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none

Subject: Tools for Outlines: M.I.C.E., The Three Act Structure
Description: Is your story about Milieu, an Idea, a Character, or an Event? Figure out what sort of story you want to tell, and see which elements are most important, how you might want to structure the story, and how to tell if you've reached the end.   Speakers include:Paul Kemner, Ericka S. Kahler, Eric S. Raymond, Michael K. Elliot, Angie Rush - Track: Literature  - Duration: 50 minutes - Audio/video needs: none
